flow.mentorSays:
Let's understand what this Error Handling challenge asks for.

**Challenge Description:**
// Add error boundary

**What we need to build:**
This challenge tests your understanding of error.tsx.

**Time estimate:** 10 minutes
**Difficulty level:** Junior

**Expected Solution Overview:**
```typescript
// app/users/error.tsx
'use client';

export default function Error({
  error,
  reset,
}: {
  error: Error;
  reset: () => void;
}) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Something went wrong!</h2>
      <p>{error.message}</p>
      <button onClick={reset}>Try again</button>
    </div>
  );
}...
```

This is a practical interview question that tests your understanding of core Angular concepts and your ability to implement them correctly.

